basics.name: Kailee Hung
basics.label: B.S. Computer Science | University of Hawaii at Manoa 2024

work.summary: Developed a pipeline for classifying and parsing annotations in clinical breast ultrasound (BUS) imaging data
highlights: Leveraged data science tools such as Python and Pandas to work with a dataset of over 100,000 images from The Hawaii & Pacific Islands Mammography Registry (HIPIMR)
Worked under the supervision of a PhD student for the University of Hawaii Cancer Center and learned about standards BUS imaging
Released as open-source software to be used as a research tool
Presented at the 2023 Summer Undergraduate Research Experience (SURE) Symposium

work.company: UH Manoa Information and Technology Services
work.summary: Contributed to the development of UI and API functionality on the UH Groupings project
highlights: Worked in an agile project management environment using Java, JavaScript, HTML, and CSS
Transitioned into role of API Lead in January 2022 which involved management of the API side of the project, along with creating and distributing new tickets on JIRA
Assisted in the creation of new features, optimizing code, fixing bugs, and increasing code coverage
Created and expanded on team documentation to aid future members
Participated in weekly meetings and code reviews
Mentored and onboarded new team members

education.institution: University of Hawaii at Manoa, Honolulu, HI
education.area: Computer Science, GPA: 4.0, Summa Cum Laude
courses: ICS 111: Introduction to Computer Science l
ICS 211: Introduction to Computer Science ll
ICS 141: Discrete Math for CS l
ICS 241: Discrete Math for CS ll
MATH 307: Linear Algebra and Differential Equations

volunteer.summary: Part of Moanalua High School's all-girls team in CyberPatriot’s National Youth Cyber Defense Competition
highlights: Competed in a team of eight for the open divison, qualifying for the platinum tier
Focused on finding and fixing security vulnerabilities in Windows and Linux operating systems

volunteer.summary: Contributed to various community service projects, some of which include:
highlights: Okinawan Festival, Oh Baby! Family Expo, Lions Club Breakfast, Recycling collection

volunteer.summary: Volunteer intern for St. Andrew's summer program
highlights: Supervised and ensured the safety and well-being of participating children
Assisted in the planning, creation, setup, and execution of meaningful activities for the children
Collaborated with other interns to help run a successful program

awards.title: Dean's List
awards.summary: Undergraduate students are awarded the Dean’s List distinction if they: (1) earn a semester grade point average of 3.5 or higher based on 12 credits or more taken for a grade, and (2) do not receive grades of W, I, F, or NC for that semester.

awards.title: Provost Achievement Scholarship
awards.summary: $40,000 scholarship distributed over 4 years at UH Manoa awarded to high-achieving Hawaii high school graduates and incoming freshman based on academics, leadership, and community service.

awards.title: Community Scholarship Fund
awards.summary: $2,625 scholarship for Hawaii residents to aid them in their academic journey.

awards.title: Summer Sophomore Merit Scholarship
awards.summary: $1,200 scholarship awarded to up to 75 UH Manoa students in recognition of their academic excellence.

awards.title: Stronger Together Hawaii Scholarship Fund
awards.summary: $3,500 scholarship awarded to selected students who participated in the Next Steps to Your Future program.

awards.title: AP Scholar with Honor
awards.summary: Granted to students who receive an average score of at least 3.25 on all AP Exams taken, and scores of 3 or higher on four or more of these exams.
